<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/2038</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-09T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>194. Your 341, May 8. For Constantinople:</p>
                        <p>Your [May] 2 in regard to difficulties made against departure from Turkey
                            of American men between 18 and 45. If the Turkish Government is in fact
                            preventing their departure the Department would be much embarrassed,
                            inasmuch as it was preparing to facilitate <pb facs="0333" n="249" xml:id="pg_249"/> the departure of unofficial Turkish subjects from
                            the United States to Bergen on May 19 by securing safe-conducts from the
                            British and French Governments. Please so inform Sublime Porte and cable
                            reply.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>